sp_scores.title: Exploit the Griffon's weakness to wind attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Griffon is vulnerable to wind, kupo, so use attacks that deal wind damage like Aero Strike to hit hard and fast!
tip_battle.title: Griffon

dungeons.epilogue: The Djinn's curse extended beyond Kazus into the walls of Castle Sasune itself. King Sasune informed the Warriors of Light that Djinn made his fastness in the Sealed Cave, but defeating him would not be simple: the king's daughter, Princess Sara, held the mythril ring they needed to banish the Djinn, and she was nowhere to be found. Fearing she may have been kidnapped by the Djinn, the Warriors of Light hurried to the Sealed Cave to rescue her.
dungeons.name: Castle Sasune
dungeons.prologue: The people of Kazus have been transformed into ghostly apparitions by the Djinn, a being of fire and darkness. Now the Warriors of Light travel to Castle Sasune in search of a mythril ring to banish the Djinn and seal him away.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Djinn's weakness to water attacks.
Exploit Djinn's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Djinn is vulnerable to ice and water attacks, kupo! Attack him with magic like Blizzard and Water!
tip_battle.title: Djinn

dungeons.epilogue: At the height of the pitched battle with the Djinn, Sara held the mythril ring aloft and he vanished in a whirl of mist--the power of the ring had sealed him away in the cave once more. After their return to Castle Sasune, the Warriors of Light placed the ring in the waters of a sacred spring, and the Djinn's curse on the people was broken. In thanks, King Sasune gave the Warriors a magic canoe, and they set out once more.
dungeons.name: Sealed Cave
dungeons.prologue: Princess Sara had not been kidnapped: she set out for the Sealed Cave on her own to banish the Djinn with the mythril ring. The Warriors of Light join her as she attempts to put an end to the Djinn's curse.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Medusa without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Medusa's Gaze can turn a character to stone, kupo! Have Stona and Esuna at the ready to cure your party! Studying Medusa's myth may give some clues to defeating her...
tip_battle.title: Medusa

dungeons.epilogue: In the Tower of Owen, the Warriors of Light found Medusa trying to destroy the tower and send the Floating Continent crashing down. Though they were successful in stopping her, the tower was damaged and might have failed had Desch's memories not returned. Realizing he was one of the Ancients and the Guardian of the Tower, he risked his life to fix the tower furnace. Thanks to his bravery, the tower was saved and the maelstrom blocking passage to the north subsided, allowing the Warriors of Light to once again take to the seas.
dungeons.name: Tower of Owen
dungeons.prologue: From the Gulgan's prophecy, the Warriors of Light have learned of the Tower of Owen, and now Desch is slowly regaining his memory, aiding their passage through the tower.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Djinn's weakness to water attacks.
Exploit Djinn's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Djinn is vulnerable to ice and water attacks, kupo! Attack him with magic like Blizzard and Water!
tip_battle.title: Djinn

dungeons.epilogue: At the height of the pitched battle with the Djinn, Sara held the mythril ring aloft and he vanished in a whirl of mist--the power of the ring had sealed him away in the cave once more. After their return to Castle Sasune, the Warriors of Light placed the ring in the waters of a sacred spring, and the Djinn's curse on the people was broken. In thanks, King Sasune gave the Warriors a magic canoe, and they set out once more.
dungeons.name: Sealed Cave
dungeons.prologue: Princess Sara had not been kidnapped: she set out for the Sealed Cave on her own to banish the Djinn with the mythril ring. The Warriors of Light join her as she attempts to put an end to the Djinn's curse.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Hein's window of weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Hein's window of weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit Hein's window of weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Hein has extremely high evasion, so it's really hard to land a physical attack on him, kupo! Not only that, every 3 turns he uses Barrier Shift to change his elemental weakness. You'll need a whole suite of fire, lightning, and ice magic to bring him down!
tip_battle.title: Hein

dungeons.epilogue: The evil wizard Hein had been using King Argus's soldiers to further his plans for world domination. The party made their way to the throne at the top of Castle Hein where they found the wizard himself, a skeletal creature descended into darkness. Though Hein's Barrier Shift made victory no certain thing, the Warriors of Light prevailed, lifting the curse on the Elder Tree of the Living Woods.
dungeons.name: Hein's Castle
dungeons.prologue: The Warriors of Light are taken captive in Tokkul and thrown in the dungeons of Castle Hein. Now they must free themselves and put an end to Hein's evil schemes.

sp_scores.title: Afflict the Giant Rat with Silence.

tip_battle.message: The Giant Rat is a vile beast with no vulnerabilities, kupo! It uses all sorts of elemental magic, so try to land a Silence on it!
tip_battle.title: Giant Rat

dungeons.epilogue: After searching the Nepto Temple, the Warriors of Light discovered that the statue of the Nepto Dragon was missing one of its eyes, a glimmering jewel. The Warriors shrank themselves to enter a passage in the statue's mouth, and soon found the Giant Rat responsible for the jewel's theft. They defeated the rat and replaced the jewel in the statue, thereby calming the Nepto Dragon who entrusted them with the Fang of Water before returning to its slumber.
dungeons.name: Nepto Temple
dungeons.prologue: The once peaceful town of Vikings' Cove has faced numerous attacks by the Nepto Dragon, which has grown violent of late. A pall lies over the village, and the Warriors of Light venture to the Nepto Temple to seek out answers.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Gutsco without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Gutsco gets 2 actions per turn, kupo! Slow or Paralyze him to keep him from running away with the victory!
tip_battle.title: Gutsco

dungeons.epilogue: The Warriors of Light defeated the thief Gutsco and retrieved the dwarves' Horn of Ice, but a mysterious shadow trailed them as they returned the horn to the altar in the Dwarven Hollows. No sooner was the horn replaced than Gutsco emerged from the shadow and stole both of the horns, which he took to the Molten Cave in order to open the path to his true goal: the Fire Crystal.
dungeons.name: Subterranean Lake
dungeons.prologue: The party arrives in the Dwarven Hollows to find the dwarves in a furor over the theft of one of their precious Horns of Ice. At the dwarves' request, the party heads for the subterranean lake to retrieve the horn.

sp_scores.title: Afflict the Giant Rat with Silence.

tip_battle.message: The Giant Rat is a vile beast with no vulnerabilities, kupo! It uses all sorts of elemental magic, so try to land a Silence on it!
tip_battle.title: Giant Rat

The Warriors shrank themselves to enter a passage in the statue's mouth, and soon found the Giant Rat responsible for the jewel's theft. They defeated the rat and replaced the jewel in the statue, thereby calming the Nepto Dragon who entrusted them with the Fang of Water before returning to its slumber.
dungeons.name: Nepto Temple
dungeons.prologue: The once peaceful town of Vikings' Cove has faced numerous attacks by the Nepto Dragon, which has grown violent of late. A pall lies over the village, and the Warriors of Light venture to the Nepto Temple to seek out answers.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Kraken's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: To stand up to the Kraken's powerful magic, you'll need abilities like Magic Break, Shell, and Reflect, kupo! The Kraken is vulnerable to lightning, though, so focus lightning attacks on this monster!
tip_battle.title: Kraken

dungeons.epilogue: The Warriors of Light arrived at the Cave of Tides to find the Kraken lying in wait for them. Like Medusa in the Tower of Owen, the Kraken was a servant of Master Xande. Though the party was successful in defeating the Kraken, the Priestess Aria died saving their lives from the creature's attack.
dungeons.name: Cave of Tides
dungeons.prologue: The power of the Water Crystal has been lost, covering the Surface World in a dark flood. The party makes for the Cave of Tides to restore the crystal's light.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Salamander's weakness to water attacks.
Exploit the Salamander's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: Salamander uses a flame attack that hits the whole party! Use its weakness to water and ice to win before your party is barbecue, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Salamander

dungeons.epilogue: The Warriors of Light made their way into the Molten Cave and defeated Gutsco, who had used the Fire Crystal to transform into the powerful Salamander. Granted new strength from the crystal, the party returned to the Dwarven Hollows where they received word that the village of Tokkul was in flames.
dungeons.name: Molten Cave
dungeons.prologue: The Warriors of Light make for the Molten Cave to settle the score with Gutsco, the thief who stole the dwarves' Horns of Ice.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Hein without being KO'd.
Win without the Black Mage being KO'd.

dungeons.prologue: The Warriors of Light are taken captive in Tokkul and thrown in the dungeons of Castle Hein. Now they must free themselves and put an end to Hein's evil schemes.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Great Tortoise without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Great Tortoise has lots of health and no real vulnerabilities, so use abilities like Armor Break and Mental Break to wear down its defenses, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Great Tortoise

dungeons.epilogue: Having survived goblin attacks and battle with the Great Tortoise, Luneth finally made his way to the altar of the Wind Crystal. The crystal enveloped him in light, and in an instant, he understood what must be done. And so the newly anointed Warrior of Light set out to drive back the darkness and restore light to the world.
dungeons.name: Altar Cave
dungeons.prologue: A young adventurer has wandered deep into the Altar Cave opened in the great earthquake. The epic journey of the Warriors of Light begins here...

sp_scores.title: Defeat Goldor without being KO'd.
Silence Goldor.

tip_battle.message: Goldor has a fondness for debuff magic, kupo! Bring along abilities that can Silence, and you'll have a much easier time!
tip_battle.title: Goldor

dungeons.epilogue: The Warriors of Light learned that Goldor, the man who chained the Enterprise, possessed a crystal. Making their way to his manor, they defeated him, but the crystal was destroyed in the fight. They retrieved the key to the chains and returned to Amur filled with regret over the crystal's loss.
dungeons.name: Goldor Manor
dungeons.prologue: As the waters recede following the death of the Kraken, the party is caught in the collapsing Cave of Tides. They wake in the Inn at Amur, miraculously alive, yet find their airship Enterprise in chains.
